<title>HONG KONG: HK SFC to issue consultation paper on share issues.</title>
<headline>HK SFC to issue consultation paper on share issues.</headline>
<dateline>HONG KONG 1997-05-23</dateline>
<text>
<p>Hong Kong's market regulator said on Friday it hoped to issue a consultation paper on share issues in June amid concerns about order in the market following the huge demand for Beijing Enterprises Holdings Ltd shares.</p>
<p>&quot;We hope to be able to have a draft in early June. We hope the consulation paper will be released in June,&quot; Anthony Neoh, chairman of the Securities and Futures Commission, told reporters.</p>
<p>The document, aimed at ensuring an orderly and fair market, will cover share issues to both retail investors in Hong Kong and institutional investors, he said.</p>
<p>-- Hong Kong Newsroom (852) 2843 6590</p>
